The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Panchkula, Sept. 4 (PTI): Former Haryana police chief S.P.S. Rathores plea for parole has been rejected by the district administration, officials said today.           
	Rathore, lodged in a Chandigarh jail and serving an 18-month term for molesting 14-year-old Ruchika Girhotra who later committed suicide, had sought a 10-day parole to get some work done on his farmland in Panchkula. The plea had been rejected after the revenue department reported that no sowing or harvesting was to be done on the land.                  
	 Calcutta: There will be no Metro service between Mahanayak Uttam Kumar and Kavi Nazrul stations on Sunday because of maintenance work.                   
	 Tirunelveli (PTI): A Chennai-based Sri Lankan Tamil refugee was arrested on Friday on charges of planning to smuggle 50-odd community members to Australia for employment, police have said. Cases under various sections of the penal code and the foreigners act were registered against 38-year-old Chandrakanthan.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): An unclaimed bag near Rajiv Chowk Metro station triggered a bomb scare in New Delhi on Saturday. It was later found to contain a computer part.                   
	Lucknow (PTI): The Uttar Pradesh government on Saturday decided to implement a revised pay scale for its 3 lakh Class IV employees in keeping with the recommendations of the Sixth Pay Commission. The hike will cost the exchequer Rs 350 crore a year.                  
	 Ratlam (PTI): Curfew was imposed in two police station areas of Ratlam in Madhya Pradesh on Saturday following arson after some people threw cow dung at a religious place. Security forces have been deployed in the troubled localities and the situation is under control, police said.                                                                                                                                              
